Ayala, Megaworld, Manila Electric: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-06-10T00:54:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/ayala-megaworld-manila-electric-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.7 percent to
4,224.34.  Property shares:  Ayala Land Inc. (ALI)  , the largest
Philippine property developer, and  Filinvest Land Inc. (FLI)  
were rated “buy” in new coverage by Citigroup Inc., which said
it sees “opportunities” in some segments of the nation’s real
estate market. The brokerage has a share-price estimate of 18.13
pesos for  Ayala Land  and a price forecast of 1.45 pesos for
Filinvest, analyst Ricardo Puig wrote in a report. Ayala Land
fell 0.1 percent to 15.18 pesos. Filinvest Land gained 0.8
percent to 1.20 pesos.  Megaworld Corp. (MEG)   was rated “sell” in new coverage
at Citigroup, which has a price estimate of 2.10 pesos,
according to Puig. The stock declined 1.9 percent to 2.04 pesos.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  : The largest Philippine power
retailer said it will work with the 37.2 billion peso ($859
million) expenditure budget that was approved by regulators for
the period from July 2011 to June 2015, a stock exchange filing
showed. The utility made the statement after regulator approved
a distribution rate that’s lower than what the company collects
from customers. The stock gained 0.9 percent to 271.40 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
